content.text:
I'll analyze both structures and provide assembly instructions for each.

Left Structure Analysis:
- 4 blocks total
- 3 layers
- Consists of two red blocks with semicircular cutouts at top and bottom, one blue cube in the middle left, and one green cube in the middle right

Right Structure Analysis:
- 8 blocks total
- 4 layers
- Base: two blue cubes
- Second layer: one yellow horizontal rectangular block
- Third layer: one red cube, one blue cube, one green cube horizontally arranged
- Top layer: two orange triangular pieces forming a roof

Assembly Instructions for Left Structure:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 2 (bottom red piece with cutout)
    Step2: Move block with index 4 (blue cube)
    Step3: Move block with index 5 (green cube)
    Step4: Move block with index 1 (top red piece with cutout)
}

Assembly Instructions for Right Structure:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 4 (left blue cube base)
    Step2: Move block with index 4 (right blue cube base)
    Step3: Move block with index 11 (yellow horizontal block)
    Step4: Move block with index 7 (red cube)
    Step5: Move block with index 4 (blue cube)
    Step6: Move block with index 5 (green cube)
    Step7: Move block with index 14 (left orange roof triangle)
    Step8: Move block with index 15 (right orange roof triangle)
}
